<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Phoenix" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Phoenix,</orth> the fabulous Arabian bird which existed single and rose again from its own ashes (used as a fem.: <bibl n="shak. pht 31" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 19.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 19, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 41</bibl>): <bibl n="shak. son 19.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 19, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pht 23" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pht 23" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 23</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 1, 32</bibl>. Not named, but alluded to in <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.424" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 424</bibl>. Denoting any thing rare and matchless: <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.182" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 182</bibl>. <cit><quote>his p. down,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 93" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 93</bibl></cit> (== matchless).<lb />Name of a house: <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 75</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 11</bibl>. Of a ship: <bibl n="shak. tn 5.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 64</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>